textOriginal:
I'm no relationship advisor, but my personal process with not being jealous of anyone or anything is understanding my self worth. Objectively, I know I'm worth enough to others, and slowly becoming worth enough to myself, and as such I'm not at all jealous of anyone my girlfriend might hang out with. If you can get like that, you might be able to drop the jealousy and come out stronger. As for whether or not she cheats on you? Just plan around that eventuality, even if you don't ever think it would happen. Just having that safety net might be enough to calm your mind.

As for being sweet and nice and shit, it's not bad to be a sweetheart to your girl on occasion, and it's pretty good to be supportive and helpful, but don't become a doormat. I'm not gonna spout that Alpha male shit because frankly it isn't important, but you do need a line in the sand. Be reasonable, fair and approachable, but not easily manipulated. At the same time, don't be a hardass unless your girlfriend likes Drill Sgt roleplay.

Hope that helps, and the best of luck to you in your future relationships!
